    public class T5<V1,V2,V3,V4,V5>
extends GridTuple5<V1,V2,V3,V4,V5>
    Defines alias for GridTuple5 by extending it. Since Java doesn't provide type aliases (like Scala, for example) we resort to these types of measures. This is intended to provide for more concise code in cases when readability won't be sacrificed. For more information see GridTuple5.
    See Also:
    GridFunc, GridTuple, Serialized Form
